entries.title: Chinese Firm Signs $540 Million Energy Deal in Afghanistan
entries.description: Beijing is expanding its presence in Central Asia after the U.S.’s exit from Afghanistan, with an eye on mineral riches.

entries.title: Inflation Threatens a French Institution: Baguettes
entries.description: Officials in France are rushing to help bakeries pay their energy bills so they can continue to bake the country’s symbolic bread.

entries.title: U.S.-Saudi Tensions Ease as Concerns About Iran Grow
entries.description: The Biden administration has dropped threats to retaliate against Saudi Arabia for an oil-production cut last year and is moving to step up security coordination to counter Iran, U.S. and Saudi officials said.

entries.title: Prince Harry Book Alleges Physical Altercation With Brother William
entries.description: Buckingham Palace was silent as it looked to weather a media storm sparked by an extract, published by the Guardian newspaper, in which Prince Harry said he was pushed to the floor.

entries.title: Rising Tensions Spark Nuclear Debate in South Korea
entries.description: President Yoon Suk-yeol pushes for Washington to allow Seoul to be more involved in management of nuclear weapons.

entries.title: Pope Francis Presides Over Funeral for Pope Benedict XVI
entries.description: Thousands of mourners gathered in St. Peter’s Square for an event that concludes the unique decadelong cohabitation of two popes in the Vatican.

entries.title: Zelensky Says Ukraine Makes Gains Outside Bakhmut but Fighting Rages Nearby
entries.description: Russian soldiers and fighters from paramilitary force Wagner have been trying to capture Bakhmut for over six months in a battle that has been costly for all involved.

entries.title: Ukraine War Spurs NATO to Improve Transport of Military Equipment
entries.description: The alliance is working with the EU to overcome enduring hurdles to moving supplies across Europe.

entries.title: Australia to Deploy U.S. Himars Rocket System Being Used in Ukraine
entries.description: The rockets will help boost Australia’s long-range strike capability.
